'''Satoru Shibata''' was the former president of [[Nintendo|Nintendo Australia]] and is now the president of [[Nintendo|Nintendo of Europe]]. When [[Shigeru Ota]] left [[Nintendo|Nintendo Europe]], Shibata was named his successor in August 2000.

He has appeared at the Nintendo Show, the DS event in Paris and Nintendo-Europe [[Wii]] Event in September 2006 and played Wii Tennis with [[Tim Henman]] and [[Greg Rusedski]], however not much is known about Shibata.

